  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?** (choose one):\r\n\r\nFEATURE REQUEST\r\n\r\n**Kubernetes version** (use `kubectl version`):\r\n\r\nHEAD\r\n\r\nNow that RBAC is going to GA, using ServiceAccounts is getting more and more important.\r\nStill a lot of users run their apps/addons/whatever in the `default` SA.\r\n\r\nIn order for the admin to be able to change ServiceAccount easily after an application has been installed (which supposedly is crashlooping due to insufficient privs), a `kubectl set serviceaccount/sa` command could exist.\r\n\r\nI know I can do this:\r\n```\r\nkubectl patch deploy <name> -p '{\"spec\":{\"template\":{\"spec\":{\"serviceAccountName\":\"<sa>\"}}}}'\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut for new users to Kubernetes, it's non-obvious.\r\n\r\nProposed command:\r\n```\r\nkubectl set [serviceaccount|sa] [deployment|rc|rs|pod] [name] [serviceaccount]\r\n```\r\n\r\nTracking issue: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/21648\r\n\r\nWDYT? @kubernetes/sig-cli-feature-requests @kubernetes/sig-auth-feature-requests @jbeda @janetkuo @adohe @smarterclayton @pwittrock \r\n\r\nThis would be a good way for a new contributor to get aquainted with the code by contributing this feature.",
